  "summary": "Keyword co-occurrence in bundled output without confirmed exfiltration path",
  "details": "Pattern matches fired on co-occurrence of the strings 'ping', 'POST', and 'hostname' in the package's bundled and source files (dist/chunk-*.cjs, dist/chunk-*.js, dist/init-*.d.ts, src/init.ts). These are generic keywords that commonly appear together in observability/telemetry tooling without indicating exfiltration: 'ping' is frequently used for health-check endpoints, 'POST' for normal HTTP client code, and 'hostname' for environment/identity reporting in telemetry payloads. No hardcoded attacker-controlled C2 endpoint, credential-path read (~/.aws, ~/.ssh, ~/.npmrc, browser profiles), env-var scraping loop, install-time lifecycle hook, or import-time side effect has been corroborated. Routing to human review so a maintainer can confirm whether the POST destinations are user-configurable / vendor-documented telemetry endpoints versus a hardcoded exfil sink.",
